The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | First magic mela in city
                                                                                                               First magic mela in city
          SEBANTI SARKAR                          Magician PC Sorcar                                   
	A Salt Lake-based organisation has conjured up the first ever magic fair in the city, to be held between March 4 and 8 at Rabindra Sadan. Magic Mela starts at 3pm on Wednesday and promises to be a one-stop destination for all things magical.        
	The fair will showcase conjuring tricks, ventriloquism, hand shadowgraph, a pavilion selling magic craft and lots more.        
	The organisers  the Federation of Indian Magic Associates (Fima)  say this was Asias first comprehensive exposition on magic.        
	The five-day national event will include magic shows by 50 magicians from West Bengal and outside, between the ages of four and 60. Magicians Rajat, Gautam Guha, Samiran, Prabhat Kiran Chowdhury, Sanjoy Chatterjee and Uday Bhaskar will be part of the show.         
	All three kinds of magic  close-up, conjuring and impromptu  will be performed in the magic arena. Magic workshops where enthusiasts can learn tricks of the trade and panel discussions are also on the cards.        
	An enclosure will be dedicated to PC Sorcar where many of his gadgets and personal belongings will be displayed.        
	Aspiring magicians looking for hats with bunnies or contraptions that can saw performers in half should head for the pavilion of magical goods. A book to teach magic to kids will be released and distributed for free at the fair. There will be no entry fee at the fair either.        
	Fimas aim is to spread awareness among professional magicians about global trends in the field and promote magic among the general public, said Tapan Karmakar, one of its directors.                                                                                                                                                                           
